      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(control-ui): honor verbose level for tool expansion",
        "body": "Fixes #49944.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Preserve the effective `chat.history.verboseLevel` returned by the gateway in Control UI state.\n- Use `chatVerboseLevel === \"full\"` to initialize chat tool-card expansion through the existing `autoExpandToolCalls` rendering path.\n- Clear stale verbose-level state on session switches and unauthorized history loads alongside the existing thinking-level state.\n- Add focused regression coverage for history loading and app render wiring.\n\n## Scope\n\nThis is intentionally limited to Control UI state/render plumbing. It does not change gateway session metadata, tool-card manual toggles, or the existing expansion-state helper behavior.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** Control UI should expand tool calls by default when the effective `chat.history.verboseLevel` for the session is `full`.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw Control UI served through the repo Vite stack at `http://127.0.0.1:5191/chat` on macOS, opened in Chromium through the Codex in-app browser, against branch head `078a32dabe2658cfb76e654a4899197f91b73334`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Started a local Control UI proof server with `node --import tsx .artifacts/openclaw-control-ui-proof.ts`, opened `http://127.0.0.1:5191/chat`, waited for the rendered session to load, then inspected the browser DOM for the rendered tool disclosure state.\n\n**Evidence after fix:** Copied live browser output from the rendered Control UI:\n\n```text\ntitle: OpenClaw Control\nurl: http://127.0.0.1:5191/chat?session=main\nbody text includes: Request: open a page and report back. ... Tool input { \"url\": \"https://example.com\" } Tool output Opened https://example.com\ntoolCards[0].className: chat-tool-msg-collapse chat-tool-msg-collapse--manual is-open\ntoolCards[0].open: true\ntoolCards[0].text: https://example.com output Browser.open with https://example.com Tool input { \"url\": \"https://example.com\" } Tool output Opened https://example.com\ntoolCards[1].className: chat-tool-card chat-tool-card--expanded\ntoolCards[1].text: Browser.open with https://example.com Tool input { \"url\": \"https://example.com\" } Tool output Opened https://example.com\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The rendered page showed the assistant tool disclosure with `chat-tool-msg-collapse--manual is-open` and the expanded tool card content visible immediately after history load, verifying the Control UI opens the tool disclosure by default when the effective session verbose level is `full`.\n\n**What was not tested:** No additional gaps.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm test ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.assistant-avatar.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.helpers.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts`\n  - Passed: 2 Vitest shards, 4 test files, 308 tests.\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 CHANGELOG.md ui/src/ui/app-render.assistant-avatar.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.helpers.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.helpers.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.ts ui/src/ui/app-view-state.ts ui/src/ui/app.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.ts ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts`\n  - Passed.\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n  - Passed.\n- `pnpm changed:lanes --json`\n  - Reports core/coreTests/docs only for the touched UI/changelog files.\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n  - Attempted, but local execution did not reach code validation because the repo delegated to Blacksmith Testbox and the local `crabbox` wrapper failed its sanity check before running the gate.\n\n## AI-assisted disclosure\n\nAI-assisted PR prepared with Codex. I reviewed the code paths touched, kept the change scoped to #49944, and ran the validation listed above.\n",
